Hero Honda, Kohinoor, MMTC, Power Grid: India Stocks Preview

-- B y   K e t a k i   G o k h a l e   a n d   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i
-- 
2011-06-02T03:20:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/hero-honda-petronet-mmtc-power-grid-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, rose
105.53, or 0.6 percent, to 18,608.81. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on
the National Stock Exchange advanced 0.6 percent to 5,592. The
BSE 200 Index increased 0.5 percent to 2,313.99. SGX S&P CNX
Nifty Index futures for June delivery retreated 1 percent to
5,536.5 as of 11:03 a.m. in  Singapore .  GMR Infrastructure Ltd. (GMRI)  : A court in  New Delhi 
ordered Delhi International Airport Pvt. to avoid charging
passengers for development fees until further notice, according
to an e-mailed statement by GMR Group, which partly owns the
airport. GMR Infrastructure declined 2.8 percent to 34.6 rupees.  Hero Honda Motors Ltd. (HH)  : India’s largest motorcycle
maker sold 500,234 units in May, compared with 435,933 a year
ago, according to an e-mailed statement. The shares rose 0.5
percent to 1,863.35 rupees.  Kohinoor Foods Ltd. (KFL)  : McCormick & Co., a U.S.-based
maker of specialty food products, has signed an agreement to
form a venture with Kohinoor Foods to market and sell its
basmati rice and food products in India, according to a
statement. Kohinoor’s shares rose 1.2 percent to 53.6 rupees.  MMTC Ltd. (MMTC)  : India’s biggest state-run trading
company invited bids to import 20,000 metric tons of  palm oil  to
ease a shortage of the commodity, the company said in a notice
on its website. The company invited offers to buy 12,000 tons of
refined, bleached and deodorized palmolein and 8,000 tons of
crude palm oil to be delivered by July 15. The shares advanced
0.2 percent to 926.9 rupees.  National Aluminium Co. (NACL IN): India’s second-biggest
producer of the metal raised prices on all grades of ingots,
sows, billets, wire rods, cast strips and rolled products by
6,000 rupees a metric ton effective from June 1, according to an
e-mailed statement yesterday. The shares gained 0.8 percent to
92.1 rupees.  Petronet LNG Ltd. (PLNG)  : India’s biggest importer of
liquefied natural gas signed an agreement to purchase the fuel
from OAO Gazprom and boost long-term contract volumes by 28
percent, the company said in an e-mailed statement yesterday.
Petronet will buy as much as 2.5 million metric tons of LNG
annually for 25 years, the company said. The shares gained 4.2
percent to 142.2 rupees.  Power Grid  Corp. of India Ltd. (PWGR IN): The board of the
nation’s largest electricity transmission company approved a
proposal to set up two pooling stations for generation projects
in Chhattisgarh state at an estimated cost of 19.6 billion
rupees ($437 million), according to a statement on the Bombay
Stock Exchange. The shares fell 0.4 percent to 100.65 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
